  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Neighboring Nations'
      title: Judgment on Neighboring Nations
      number: 1
      content: '  The words of Amos, who was among the sheepherders of Tekoa, which
        he saw [in a divine revelation] concerning Israel in the days of Uzziah king
        of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel, two
        years before the earthquake.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said,\u201CThe Lord thunders and roars from Zion [in judgment]And
        utters His voice from Jerusalem;Then the pastures of the shepherds mourn,And
        the summit of [Mount] Carmel dries up [because of God\u2019s judgment].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CFor three transgressions of Damascus and
        for four (multiplied delinquencies)I shall not reverse its punishment or
        revoke My word concerning it,Because they have threshed Gilead [east of the
        Jordan River] with sharp iron sledges [having spikes that crushed and shredded].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So I will send a fire [of war, conquest, and destruction] upon the
        house of Hazael,And it shall devour the palaces and strongholds of Ben-hadad
        (Hazael\u2019s son).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I also will break the bar [of the gate] of Damascus,And cut off and
        destroy the inhabitant from the Valley of Aven (Wickedness),And the ruler
        who holds the scepter, from Beth-eden (Damascus);And the people of Aram [conquered
        by the Assyrians] will go into exile to Kir,\u201DSays the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CFor three transgressions of Gaza [in Philistia]
        and for four (multiplied delinquencies)I will not reverse its punishment
        or revoke My word concerning it,Because [as slave traders] they took captive
        the entire [Jewish] population [of defenseless Judean border villages, of
        which none was spared]And deported them to Edom [for the slave trade].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So I will send a fire [of war, conquest, and destruction] on the
        wall of GazaAnd it shall consume her citadels.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And I will cut off and destroy the inhabitants from Ashdod,And the
        ruler who holds the scepter, from Ashkelon;And I will unleash My power and
        turn My hand [in judgment] against Ekron,And the rest of the Philistines
        [in Gath and the towns dependent on these four Philistine cities] shall die,\u201DSays
        the Lord God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CFor three transgressions of Tyre and for
        four (multiplied delinquencies)I will not reverse its punishment or revoke
        My word concerning it,Because they [as middlemen] deported an entire [Jewish]
        population to EdomAnd did not [seriously] remember their covenant of brotherhood.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So I will send a fire [of war, conquest, and destruction] on the
        wall of Tyre,And it shall consume her citadels.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CFor three transgressions of Edom [the descendants
        of Esau] and for four (multiplied delinquencies)I will not reverse its punishment
        or revoke My word concerning it,Because he pursued his brother Jacob (Israel)
        with the sword,Corrupting and stifling his compassions and casting off all
        mercy;His destructive anger raged continually,And he maintained [and nurtured]
        his wrath forever.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So I will send a fire [of war, conquest, and destruction] upon Teman,And
        it shall consume the citadels of Bozrah [in Edom].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CFor three transgressions of the children
        of Ammon and for four (multiplied delinquencies)I will not reverse its punishment
        or revoke My word concerning it,Because the Ammonites have ripped open the
        pregnant women of Gilead,That they might enlarge their border.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So I will kindle a fire [of war, conquest, and destruction] on the
        wall of Rabbah [in Ammon]And it shall devour its strongholdsAmid war cries
        and shouts of alarm on the day of battle,And a tempest on the day of the
        whirlwind [when the enemy captures the city].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Their king shall go into exile,He and his princes together,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Moab'
      title: Judgment on Moab
      number: 1
      content: "  Thus says the Lord,\u201CFor three transgressions of Moab and for
        four (multiplied delinquencies)I will not reverse its punishment or revoke
        My word concerning it,Because he burned the bones of the king of Edom [Esau\u2019s
        descendant] into lime [and used it to plaster a Moabite house].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I will send a fire [of war, conquest, and destruction] upon MoabAnd
        it shall devour the strongholds of Kerioth;And Moab shall die amid tumult
        and uproar,With war cries and shouts of alarm and the sound of the trumpet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Judgment on Judah'
      title: Judgment on Judah
      number: 3
      content: "I will also cut off and destroy the ruler from its midstAnd slay
        all the princes with him,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CFor three transgressions of Judah and for
        four (multiplied delinquencies)I will not reverse its punishment or revoke
        My word concerning it,Because they have rejected the law of the Lord [the
        sum of God\u2019s instruction to His people]And have not kept His commandments;But
        their lies [and their idols], after which their fathers walked,Caused them
        to go astray.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Judgment on Israel'
      title: Judgment on Israel
      number: 5
      content: "So I will send a fire [of war, conquest, and destruction by the Babylonians]
        upon JudahAnd it will devour the strongholds of Jerusalem.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CFor three transgressions of Israel and for
        four (multiplied delinquencies)I will not reverse its punishment or revoke
        My word concerning it,Because they sell the righteous and innocent for silverAnd
        the needy for the price of a pair of sandals.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'These who pant after (long to see) the dust of the earth on the head
        of the helpless [as sign of their grief and distress]Also turn aside the
        way of the humble;And a man and his father will go to the same girlSo that
        My holy name is profaned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They stretch out beside every [pagan] altar on clothes taken in pledge
        [to secure a loan, disregarding God\u2019s command],And in the house of their
        God [in contempt of Him] they frivolously drink the wine [which has been]
        taken from those who have been fined.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYet it was I [not the false gods] who destroyed the Amorite
        before them,Though his height was like the height of the cedars,And he was
        as strong as the oaks;I even destroyed his fruit above and his root below.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Also it was I who brought you up out of the land of Egypt,And I led
        you forty years through the wildernessThat you might possess the land of
        the Amorite.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then I raised up some of your sons to be prophets [who gave you My
        revelation],And some of your young men to be Nazirites (dedicated ones).Is
        this not true, O you children of Israel?\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CBut you gave the Nazirites wine to drink [despite their vows]And
        commanded the prophets, saying, \u2018You shall not prophesy!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Behold, I am weighted down beneath youAs a cart that is weighted
        down when it is full of sheaves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Flight will be lost to the swift [so they will be unable to escape],And
        the strong shall not strengthen nor maintain his power,Nor shall the mighty
        man save his own life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He who handles the bow will not stand his ground,The one who is swift
        of foot will not escape,Nor will he who rides the horse save his life [from
        the invading army].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Even the bravest among the warriors shall flee naked on that day,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: All the Families Are Guilty'
      title: All the Families Are Guilty
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear this word that the Lord has spoken against you, O children
        of Israel, against the whole family which I brought up from the land of Egypt:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI have known [chosen, cared for, and loved] only you of all
        the families of the earth;Therefore I shall punish you for all your wickedness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Do two men walk together unless they have made an appointment?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Does a lion roar in the forest when he has no prey?Does a young lion
        growl from his den if he has not captured something?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Does a bird fall into a trap on the ground when there is no bait
        in it?Does a trap spring up from the ground when it has caught nothing at
        all? [Of course not! So it is that Israel has earned her impending judgment.]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'If a trumpet is blown in a city [warning of danger] will not the
        people tremble?If a disaster or misfortune occurs in a city has not the Lord
        caused it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Surely the Lord God does nothing  Without revealing His secret plan
        [of the judgment to come]To His servants the prophets.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The lion has roared! Who will not fear?The Lord God has spoken [to
        the prophets]! Who can but prophesy?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Proclaim on the fortresses in Ashdod (Philistia) and on the citadels
        in the land of Egypt, and say, \u201CAssemble yourselves on the mountains
        of Samaria, and see the great confusion within her and the oppressions and
        abuse of authority in her midst. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For they do not know how to do right,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthese
        who store up violence and devastation [like treasures] in their strongholds.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore, thus says the Lord God,\u201CAn adversary (Assyria), even
        one surrounding the land,Shall pull down your strength from youAnd your fortresses
        will be looted.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CJust as the shepherd snatches from the mouth
        of the lion a couple of legs or a piece of the [sheep\u2019s] ear [to prove
        to the owner that he has not stolen the animal],So will the [remaining] children
        of Israel living in Samaria be snatched awayWith the corner of a bed and
        [part of] the damask covering of a couch.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Hear and testify against the house of Jacob,\u201DSays the Lord God,
        the God of hosts,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201COn that day when I punish Israel\u2019s transgressions,I shall
        also punish the altars of Bethel [with their golden calves];And the horns
        of the altar shall be cut offAnd fall to the ground.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And I shall tear down the winter house with the summer house;And
        the houses of ivory shall also perishAnd the great houses shall come to an
        end,\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: \u201CYet You Have Not Returned to Me\u201D"
      title: "\u201CYet You Have Not Returned to Me\u201D"
      number: 1
      content: "  Hear this word, you [well-fed, pampered] cows (women) of Bashan
        who are on the mountain of Samaria,Who oppress the poor, who crush the needy,Who
        say to their husbands, \u201CBring [the wine] now, and let us drink!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Lord God has sworn [an oath] by His holinessThat, \u201CBehold,
        the days are coming upon youWhen they shall take you away with meat hooks,And
        the last of you with fish hooks.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And you shall go out through the breaches [made in the city wall],Every
        woman straight before her [unable to turn aside],And you shall be cast to
        Harmon,\u201DSays the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CCome to Bethel [where the golden calf is] and transgress;In
        Gilgal [where idols are worshiped] multiply transgression;Bring your sacrifices
        every morning,Your tithes every three days!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  Offer [by burning] a sacrifice of thanksgiving of that which is
        leavened,And [boastfully] proclaim freewill offerings, announce them.For
        this you so love to do, O children of Israel!\u201DSays the Lord God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI also gave you cleanness of teeth [because of the famine]
        in all your citiesAnd lack of bread in all your places,Yet you have not returned
        to Me [in repentance],\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CFurthermore, I withheld the rain from youWhen there were still
        three months until the harvest.Then I would send rain on one city,And on
        another city I would not send rain;One piece of ground was rained on,While
        the part not rained on would dry up.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So [the people of] two or three cities would stagger into one city
        to drink water,But would not be satisfied;Yet you have not returned to Me
        [in repentance],\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CI wounded you with blight [from the hot, blasting east wind]
        and with mildew;And the caterpillar devouredYour many gardens and vineyards,
        your fig trees and your olive trees;Yet you have not returned to Me [in repentance],\u201D
        says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CI sent a plague among you like [those of] Egypt;I killed your
        young men with the sword and I captured your horses,I made the stench of
        your camp rise up into your nostrils;Yet you have not returned to Me [in
        repentance],\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI overthrew and destroyed [some among] you, as [I, your] God
        overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah,And you were [rescued] like a log pulled out
        of the flame;Yet you have not returned to Me [in repentance],\u201D says
        the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTherefore this is what I shall do to you, O Israel;Because
        I will do this to you,Prepare to meet your God [in judgment], O Israel!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For behold, He who forms the mountains and creates the windAnd declares
        to man what are His thoughts,He who makes the dawn into darknessAnd treads
        on the heights of the earth\u2014The Lord God of hosts is His name."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: \u201CSeek Me that You May Live\u201D"
      title: "\u201CSeek Me that You May Live\u201D"
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear this word which I take up for you as a funeral song, O house
        of Israel:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "She has fallen, she will not rise again\u2014The virgin Israel.She
        lies neglected on her land;There is no one to raise her up.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For thus says the Lord God,\u201CThe city which goes forth a thousand
        strongWill have a hundred left,And the one which goes forth a hundred strongWill
        have ten left to the house of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus says the Lord to the house of Israel,\u201CSeek Me [search
        diligently for Me and regard Me as more essential than food] so that you
        may live.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But do not resort to Bethel [to worship the golden calf]Nor enter
        [idolatrous] Gilgal,Nor cross over to Beersheba [and its idols];For Gilgal
        will certainly go into captivity and exile,And Bethel will come to nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Seek the Lord [search diligently for Him and long for Him as your
        most essential need] so that you may live,Or He will rush down like a [devouring]
        fire, O house of Joseph,And there will be no one to quench the flame for
        [idolatrous] Bethel,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For those [shall be consumed] who turn justice into wormwood (bitterness)And
        cast righteousness down to the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He who made the [cluster of stars called] Pleiades and [the constellation]
        Orion,Who turns deep darkness into the morningAnd darkens the day into night,Who
        calls for the waters of the seaAnd pours them out on the surface of the earth,The
        Lord is His name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'It is He who causes [sudden] destruction to flash forth on the strongSo
        that destruction comes on the fortress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They hate the one who reprimands [the unrighteous] in the [court
        held at the city] gate [regarding him as unreasonable and rejecting his reprimand],And
        they detest him who speaks [the truth] with integrity and honesty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore, because you impose heavy rent on the poorAnd demand a
        tribute (food-tax) of grain from them,Though you have built [luxurious] houses
        of square stone,You will not live in them;You have planted beautiful vineyards,
        but you will not drink their wine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For I know your transgressions are many and your sins are great (shocking,
        innumerable),You who distress the righteous and take bribes,And turn away
        from the poor in the [court of the city] gate [depriving them of justice].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore, he who is prudent and has insight will keep silent at
        such a [corrupt and evil] time, for it is an evil time [when people will
        not listen to truth and will disregard those of good character].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Seek (long for, require) good and not evil, that you may live;And
        so may the Lord God of hosts be with you,Just as you have said!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Hate evil and love good,And establish justice in the [court of the
        city] gate.Perhaps the Lord God of hostsWill be gracious to the remnant of
        Joseph [that is, those who remain after God\u2019s judgment].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore, thus says the Lord God of hosts, the Lord,\u201CThere
        is wailing in all the public plazas,And in all the streets they say, \u2018Alas!
        Alas!\u2019And they call the farmers to mourning [for those who have died]And
        professional mourners to wailing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And in all vineyards there is wailing,For I will pass through your
        midst [in judgment],\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Woe (judgment is coming) to you who desire the day of the Lord [expecting
        rescue from the Gentiles]!Why would you want the day of the Lord?It is darkness
        (judgment) and not light [and rescue and prosperity];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'It is as if a man runs from a lion [escaping one danger]And a bear
        meets him [so he dies anyway],Or goes home, and leans with his hand against
        the wallAnd a snake bites him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Will not the day of the Lord be darkness, instead of light,Even very
        dark with no brightness in it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CI hate, I despise and reject your [sacred] feasts,And I do
        not take delight in your solemn assemblies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Even though you offer Me your burnt offerings and your grain offerings,I
        will not accept them;And I will not even look at the peace offerings of your
        fattened animals.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Take the noise of your songs away from Me [they are an irritation]!I
        shall not even listen to the melody of your harps.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But let justice run down like watersAnd righteousness like an ever-flowing
        stream [flowing abundantly].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CDid you bring Me sacrifices and grain offerings during those
        forty years in the wilderness, O house of Israel? [Certainly not!] "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'You carried along your king Sikkuth and Kayyun [your man-made gods
        of Saturn], your images of your star-god which you made for yourselves [but
        you brought Me none of the appointed sacrifices]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Therefore, I will send you to go into exile far beyond Damascus,\u201D
        says the Lord, whose name is the God of hosts."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: \u201CThose at Ease in Zion\u201D"
      title: "\u201CThose at Ease in Zion\u201D"
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe (judgment is coming) to those who are at ease and carefree
        in Zion (Judah)And to those on the mountain of Samaria who feel secure,The
        distinguished men of the foremost of nations,To whom the house of Israel
        comes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Go over to Calneh [in Babylonia] and look,And from there go [north
        of Damascus] to the great city of Hamath;Then go down to Gath of the Philistines.Are
        they better than these kingdoms [of yours],Or is their territory greater
        than yours?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Do you put off the day of punishment,Yet cause the seat of violence
        to come near?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Those who lie on [luxurious] beds of ivoryAnd lounge around out on
        their couches,And eat lambs from the flockAnd calves from the midst of the
        stall,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Who improvise to the sound of the harp\u2014Like David they have
        composed songs for themselves\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Who drink wine from sacrificial bowlsAnd anoint themselves with the
        finest oils [reflecting their unrestrained celebration];Yet they are not
        grieved over the ruin of Joseph (Israel).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore, they will now go into exile with the first of the captives,And
        the cultic revelry and banqueting of those who lounge around [on their luxurious
        couches] will pass away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Lord God has sworn [an oath] by Himself\u2014the Lord God of
        hosts, says:\u201CI loathe and reject the [self-centered] arrogance of Jacob
        (Israel),And I hate his palaces and citadels;Therefore, I shall hand over
        the [idolatrous] city [of Samaria] with all that it contains [to the Assyrian
        invaders].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And it shall come to pass that if there remain ten men in one house,
        they shall die [by the pestilence that comes with war]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then one\u2019s uncle, or his undertaker, shall come to bring the
        [disease-infected] body out of the house, [to cremate it], and he will say
        to another in the farthest part of the house, \u201CIs there anyone else
        with you?\u201D And that one will say, \u201CNo one.\u201D Then he will respond,
        \u201CHush! Keep quiet! For the name of the Lord is not to be mentioned [even
        casually, for fear that we might invoke even more punishment].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For behold, the Lord is going to command that the great house be
        smashed to pieces and the small house to fragments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Do horses run on rocks?Do men plow rocks with oxen? [Of course not!]Yet
        you have turned justice into poisonAnd the fruit of righteousness into wormwood
        (bitterness),  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You who [self-confidently] rejoice in Lo-debar (Nothing),Who say,
        \u201CHave we not by our own strength taken Karnaim (Strength) for ourselves?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CFor behold, I am going to stir up a nation against you,O house
        of Israel,\u201D says the Lord, the God of hosts,\u201CAnd they will afflict
        and torment you [to the entire limits of Israel] from the entrance of Hamath
        [in the north]To the brook of the Arabah [in the south].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warning Through Visions'
      title: Warning Through Visions
      number: 1
      content: "  Thus the Lord God showed me [a vision], and behold, He was forming
        a swarm of locusts when the spring crop began to sprout. And behold, the
        spring crop was after the king\u2019s mowing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And when the locusts had finished eating the plants of the land,
        then I said,\u201CO Lord God, please forgive!How can Jacob stand,For he is
        so small [that he cannot endure this]?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The Lord revoked this sentence.\u201CIt shall not take place,\u201D
        said the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Thus the Lord God showed me, and behold, the Lord God called for
        punishment with fire, and it devoured the great deep [underground sources
        of water] and began to consume the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then I said,\u201CO Lord God, please stop!How can Jacob stand,For
        he is so small [that he cannot endure this]?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The Lord revoked this sentence.\u201CThis also shall not be,\u201D
        said the Lord God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Thus He showed me [a vision], and behold, the Lord was standing by
        a vertical wall with a plumb line in His hand [to determine if the wall was
        straight or if it needed to be destroyed]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Lord said to me, \u201CAmos, what do you see?\u201D And I said,
        \u201CA plumb line.\u201D Then the Lord said,\u201CBehold, I am setting a
        plumb line [as a standard]Among My people Israel [showing the defectiveness
        of the nation, requiring judgment].I shall not spare them any longer. [The
        door of mercy is shut.]  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Amos Accused, Answers'
      title: Amos Accused, Answers
      number: 9
      content: "And the [idolatrous] high places of Isaac (Israel) will be devastated
        and deserted,And the sanctuaries of Israel will be in ruins.Then I shall
        rise up against the house of Jeroboam with the sword [and destroy the monarchy].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Amaziah, the priest of Bethel [site of the golden calf shrine],
        sent word to Jeroboam king of Israel, saying, \u201CAmos has conspired against
        you in the midst of the house of Israel; the land is unable to endure all
        his words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For in this way Amos has said, \u2018Jeroboam will die by the sword
        and Israel will certainly go from its land into exile.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Amaziah said to Amos, \u201CGo, you seer, run for your life
        [from Israel] to the land of Judah [your own country] and eat bread and live
        as a prophet there! "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But do not prophesy any longer at Bethel, for it is the king\u2019s
        sanctuary and a royal residence.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Amos replied to Amaziah, \u201CI am not a prophet [by profession],
        nor am I a prophet\u2019s son; I am a herdsman and a grower of sycamore figs. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But the Lord took me as I followed the flock and the Lord said to
        me, \u2018Go, prophesy to My people Israel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now therefore, listen to the word of the Lord: You say, \u2018You
        shall not prophesy against Israel nor shall you speak against the house of
        Isaac.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Therefore, thus says the Lord, \u2018Your wife shall become a prostitute
        in the city [when the Assyrians capture Samaria] and your sons and your daughters
        shall fall by the sword, and your land shall be divided by a measuring line;
        you yourself shall die in an unclean and defiled [pagan] land, and Israel
        shall certainly go from its land into exile.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Basket of Fruit and Israel\u2019s Captivity"
      title: "Basket of Fruit and Israel\u2019s Captivity"
      number: 1
      content: '  Thus the Lord God showed me [a vision], and behold, there was a
        basket of [overripe] summer fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And He said, \u201CAmos, what do you see?\u201D And I said, \u201CA
        basket of summer fruit.\u201D Then the Lord said to me, \u201CThe end has
        come for My people Israel. I will spare them no longer [for the nation is
        ripe for judgment]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "In that day, the songs of the palace shall turn to wailing,\u201D
        says the Lord God. \u201CThere will be many dead bodies; in [sacred] silence
        they will throw them everywhere.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hear this, you who trample down the needy, and do away with the poor
        of the land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "saying,\u201CWhen will the New Moon [festival] be overSo that we
        may sell grain,And the Sabbath ended so that we may open the wheat market,Making
        the ephah [measure] smaller and the shekel bigger [that is, selling less
        for a higher price]And to cheat by falsifying the scales,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So that we may buy the poor [as slaves] for silver [since they are
        unable to support themselves]And the needy for a pair of sandals,And that
        we may sell the leftovers of the wheat [as if it were a good grade of grain]?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Lord has sworn [an oath] by the pride of Jacob,\u201CSurely I
        shall never forget [nor leave unpunished] any of their [rebellious] acts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Because of this [coming judgment] will the land not quakeAnd everyone
        mourn who dwells in it?Indeed, all of it shall rise up like the Nile,And
        it will be tossed around [from the impact of judgment]And [afterward] subside
        again like the Nile of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "It shall come about in that day,\u201D says the Lord God,\u201CThat
        I shall cause the sun to go down at noon,And I shall darken the earth in
        broad daylight.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And I shall turn your festivals and feasts into mourningAnd all your
        songs into dirges (funeral poems to be sung);And I shall cause sackcloth
        to be put on everyone\u2019s loinsAnd baldness on every head [shaved for
        mourning].And I shall make that time like a time of mourning for an only
        son [who has died],And the end of it shall be like a bitter day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord God,\u201CWhen
        I will send hunger over the land,Not hunger for bread or a thirst for water,But
        rather [a hunger] for hearing the words of the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'People shall stagger from sea to sea [to the very ends of the earth]And
        from the north even to the east;They will roam here and there to seek the
        word of the Lord [longing for it as essential for life],But they will not
        find it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'In that day the beautiful virginsAnd [even the vigorous] young men
        shall faint from thirst.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Those who swear [their oaths] by the sin (guilt) of Samaria or Ashimah
        (a pagan goddess),Who say, \u2018By the life of your god [the golden calf],
        O Dan!\u2019And [swear], \u2018By the life of the way of [idolatrous] Beersheba,\u2019They
        shall fall and not rise again.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Judgment Unavoidable"
      title: "God\u2019s Judgment Unavoidable"
      number: 1
      content: "  I saw [in a vision] the Lord standing at the altar, and He said,\u201CDestroy
        the capitals (tops) of the pillars so that the thresholds will shake,And
        break them on the heads of all of the people!Then I will kill the rest of
        them with the sword;They will not have a fugitive who will get away,Or a
        survivor who will escape.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Though they dig into Sheol [to hide in the deepest pit],From there
        My hand will take them [for judgment];And though they climb up to heaven
        [to hide in the realm of light],From there will I bring them down [for judgment].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Though they hide on the summit of [Mount] Carmel,I will track them
        down and take them from there;And though they hide from My sight on the floor
        of the sea,From there I shall command the serpent and it will bite them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And though they go into captivity before their enemies,From there
        I shall command the sword to kill them,And I will set My eyes against them
        for evil (judgment, punishment) and not for good [that is, not for correction
        leading to restoration].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord God of hosts [the Omnipotent Ruler],It is He who touches
        the earth [in judgment] and it melts,And all who dwell on it mourn [in despair
        and fear],And all of it rises up like the NileAnd subsides like the Nile
        of Egypt;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "It is He who builds His upper chambers in the heavensAnd has established
        His vaulted dome (the firmament of heaven) over the earth,He who calls to
        the waters of the seaAnd pours them out on the face of the earth\u2014The
        Lord is His name.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAre you [degenerate ones] not as the [despised] sons of Ethiopia
        to Me,O sons of Israel?\u201D says the Lord.\u201CHave I not brought up Israel
        from the land of Egypt,And the Philistines from Caphtor and the Arameans
        (Syrians) from Kir?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Behold, the eyes of the Lord God are on the sinful [northern] kingdom
        [of Israel\u2019s ten tribes]And I shall destroy it from the face of the
        earth;But I shall not totally destroy the house of Jacob [that is, the entire
        nation of Israel],\u201DSays the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CFor behold, I am commanding,And I shall shake and sift the
        house of Israel among all nations [and cause it to tremble]Like grain is
        shaken in a sieve [removing the chaff],But not a kernel [of the faithful
        remnant] shall fall to the ground and be lost [from My sight].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Restoration of Israel'
      title: The Restoration of Israel
      number: 10
      content: "All the sinners among My people will die by the sword,Those who say
        [defiantly], \u2018The disaster will not overtake or confront us.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CIn that day I shall raise up and restore the fallen tabernacle
        (booth) of David,And wall up its breaches [in the city walls];I will also
        raise up and restore its ruinsAnd rebuild it as it was in the days of old,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "That they may possess the remnant of Edom (ancient enemies)And all
        the nations that are called by My name,\u201DSays the Lord who does this.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CWhen
        the plowman shall overtake the one who gathers the harvest,And the one who
        treads the grapes [shall overtake] him who sows the seed [for the harvest
        continues until planting time];When the mountains will drip sweet wineAnd
        all the hills shall melt [that is, everything that was once barren will overflow
        with streams of blessing].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Also I shall bring back the exiles of My people Israel,And they will
        rebuild the deserted and ruined cities and inhabit them:They will also plant
        vineyards and drink their wine,And make gardens and eat their fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I will also plant them on their land,And they shall never again be
        uprooted from their landWhich I have given them,\u201DSays the Lord your
        God."
      comments: []
